ContainedObjects.Description: When sharing cards, you share (face up) before your allies.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: If you share 3 cards, you may draw 1 element.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: The final obstacle and reward is always face up on your turn.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: When sharing cards, your allies share (face up) before you.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: Choose an element (except luck). On your turn you may discard a card in lieu of your specialist element.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: Your max hand does not change as you lose morale. You start with half the normal morale, and this is your maximum.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: You may share between zero and four cards.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: Once per turn, if you would fail an obstacle you may lose one personnel to shuffle that obstacle back into the obstacles deck and replace it with the top one from the deck. You are now engaged with that new obstacle.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: Credits you accumulate do not need to be spent immediately.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: After the pooling step on your turn, you may look at all the rewards.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: On your turn, you may use two of the same element from your hand in place of a luck.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: Draw two element cards for each event that causes morale loss. You have no max hand size and no longer draw element cards in between rounds.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: Once per turn, you may pay 1 credit to increase your morale by two. You may not go above your maximum.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: If in a turn you would lose more than one personnel, lose one fewer.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: You can only share 1 card. Two cards are drawn from the basic elements deck and added to the pool when you share.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: Roll a D6 at the start of your turn. On the roll of a 2, 3, or 4 you start on that obstacle.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: Your hand size is one greater than your current personnel.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: You may announce which card you are sharing aloud before anyone contributes to the pool. You need not be honest.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: You may look at the active player's hand while they're blindfolded. You may not share this information.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: Once per turn you may discard doubles of an element from your hand to draw 3 new elements at any time.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: On your turn you may look at one facedown card (including macguffins).
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: You may lose 2 personnel to gain 1 credit. You can still only buy from the market during your buy phase.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: You may discard X cards to look at the top 2X cards of any deck. Put them back on the top or bottom of that deck in any order.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: You approach obstacles in reverse order. You cannot disengage unless you have lost at least 1 personnel.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: You may waste your turn to return your morale to max.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: You may discard two cards to draw a card from the reward deck to your hand at any time.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: When you draw basic element cards, draw 2 extra and then discard 2 cards.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: You may generate a luck symbol by asking your allies to discard a total of three cards, divided among the players as you choose.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: You may generate a luck symbol by forcing your allies to discard a total of three cards, divided among the players as you choose. You cannot ask permission to do this, nor give them warning.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: You may give a card from your hand to another player at any time.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: You choose who is first player each round. That player draws an extra element card.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: Once during your turn you may refresh the market.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: If you play a power card from your hand to overcome an obstacle, you may return it to your hand.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: You may play a combat card from your hand to overcome any obstacle at the cost of 1 personel.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: You may skip over any obstacle involving covert ops. Don't lose personnel, but also don't take the reward.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: Cards played to overcome obstacles involving science carry over to subsequent obstacles in that turn. (Except luck.)
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: At the end of your turn, you may discard a diplomacy card to draw the top card of the reward deck into your hand.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card

ContainedObjects.Description: When another player encounters an obstacle involving air support, you may offer 1 or 2 cards to help overcome that obstacle.
ContainedObjects.Name: Card
